that were interested in the Y program. As best I can

07:57.412 --> 08:06.102
describe, it was the college version of the Hi-Y 
that was in the high schools. In the basement of the

08:06.689 --> 08:12.757
YMCA, there was, at one time, there was a swimming 
pool. And it was not a... It was there until they

08:15.741 --> 08:17.744
built the P.L. Downs Natatorium. And can you 
relate about what year that might have been to you?

08:24.353 --> 08:26.115
I'm guessing it was about 1936. Okay, so... But the 
pool was, it was just a big bathtub. It didn't have a

08:31.843 --> 08:34.607
circuitry system in it. And once a week, they 
had... drain it, scrub the walls, and then refill

08:36.659 --> 08:40.143
it. And that was the only time that I ever got to swim 
in it. It had been drained because it was over my

08:45.209 --> 08:50.055
head. And I got to play in it until the water got deep 
enough that I couldn't stand up and then I had to get

08:50.115 --> 08:57.003
out. So about once a week I got to go swim. About what 
dimensions? The pool was... Well, it was the size

09:04.334 --> 09:08.438
of three bowling alleys. Because when they built 
the P.L. Dow Junior Natatorium, they covered the

09:11.721 --> 09:20.549
pool over and put three bowling alleys in the area 
where the pool had been. In addition to the bowling

09:20.649 --> 09:33.801
alleys, they had pool tables downstairs, there 
was a barber shop, and Casey's Confectionary,

09:20.649 --> 09:33.801
which was a privately run soda fountain. Could you 
buy sandwiches and burgers? Sandwiches and

09:38.738 --> 09:40.821
burgers and ice cream. Let's see. What that would 
be normal things today would not have been so. No

09:47.250 --> 09:47.851
beer. Tobacco? Yeah, cigarettes. Tobacco and

09:53.339 --> 10:00.589
then just soda fountain types of sandwiches. I 
don't think they had hamburgers, but they had They

10:03.751 --> 10:10.419
had sandwiches and ice cream, fountain drinks. 
